        <ontology:is_identified_by rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/appellation/Arbutus_unedo_tree_fruit_from_mountain_hillsides_and_surroundings"/>
        <ontology:partOfNarrative rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N250_VC_14_PT2"/>
        <ontology:took_place_at rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/phenomenal_place/38.7_-9.183333333333334"/>
        <ontology:hasDescription>The MOVING reference member state of this VC (Value Chain) is PORTUGAL ESTRELA. The reference MOVING Card ID of this VC is VC 14 PT2. At Serra da Estrela hillsides and surroundings, Stawberry tree occurs spontaneously and in planted orchards. Stawberry tree is exploited mainly because of its fruit, that is harvested and used to produce brandy. Stawberry tree fruit is used locally or sold to other regions in Portugal. Stawberry tree fruit brandy is sold at national and international levels.  </ontology:hasDescription>
    </NamedIndividual>
    


