        <ontology:partOfNarrative rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N250_VC_14_PT2"/>
        <ontology:took_place_at rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/phenomenal_place/40.42203_-7.70245"/>
        <ontology:took_place_at rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/place/0"/>
        <ontology:hasDescription>The reference mountain chain of this VC is Cordilheira Central (RR08). The reference mountain landscape of this VC is Seia. Located on the western slope of Serra da Estrela, Seia is a municipality with 21 parishes, in the district of Guarda in the Centre region of Portugal. Seia shares with the municipalities of Covilhã and Manteigas, the highest point in mainland Portugal at 1993 meters of altitude. Seia has a strong industrial tradition, mainly related to textiles and the distribution of electricity. The production of sheep&amp;apos;s cheese is also a tradition.  </ontology:hasDescription>
    </NamedIndividual>
    


